ster data from affecting other tests.\n\nNow examining the RST section structure in the source file more carefully. I'm seeing various heading levels marked with different underline characters like `====` and `----`, and I need to understand the hierarchy properly to identify any structural issues. Looking at the hints for section 5, I see \"セルの書式\", \"文字列書式\", and \"セル文字列設\" which cover the formatting concepts mentioned in the source. For section 6, the hints include \"セルへの特殊な記述方法\", \"null値\", \"空文字列\", \"真偽値\" — these align with the special notation methods described. Section 7's hints cover \"注意事項\", \"テスト独立性\", \"Excelシート記述\" which match the key points about test independence and data management. The hint coverage looks comprehensive across all sections. s7の注意事項セクションにはテスト実行順序やテストデータ管理、マスタデータ関連の項目が揃っているようだ。`master_data_setup_tool`という記述も見かけたが、`MasterDataRestore`で十分にカバーされている。\n\n特殊記法のテーブルをもう一度確認してみると、改行コードについてのExcelの仕様に関する注釈があるようだが、既に「改行コード」のヒントで対応できている。\n\n全体的に見ると、知識ファイルは重大な漏れや誤りなく、ソース内容を正確に反映しているようだ。 Looking at the knowledge file more carefully, I notice it covers the main points about empty strings and line breaks, though it's missing some of the specific benefits of the master data approach that the source mentions—like improved maintainability and faster test execution. These are useful details but not critical to the core documentation. I should flag the missing benefits as a minor omission since they're substantive reasons that would help answer why this approach is used, even though the implementation details are captured in the knowledge file. project-wide reuse, easy maintenance, faster test execution)\n\nActually, this is quite minor. Let me check if there's anything else...\n\nOne more thing - the source provides an actual example of SETUP_TABLE:\n```\nSETUP_TABLE=COMPOSER\n+--------+------------+-----------+\n|     NO | FIRST_NAME | LAST_NAME |\n```\n\nThe knowledge file mentions the format but doesn't include this concrete example. This is borderline